Important Information:

Homecoming is set for Friday, September 18th 2020. Freshman Class will need to start looking and picking up tree limbs/brush. Please take it to the location of Bonfire. Please remember to wear your masks! Sophomore Class will need to put a Dummie together and Junior Class will need to start looking or making an Outhouse.
Class cookout will be around the bonfire as before. This year each class will be assigned a spot. Each class will need to stay with their own class to help practice social distancing. Cookout & Bonfire will be on Wednesday. Each class is responsible for when and what you plan on eating. Bonfire will start at dark thirty. Homecoming Dress Up Days will be posted a little later.

post_text:
Paducah ISD welcomes our new staff members, Mrs. Erica Lewis and Mrs. Tara Sandusky.
We are very excited for both of these ladies to be here and become Dragons again.
Mrs. Lewis is rejoining us following a one year teaching stint at Fort Stockton ISD. She will be teaching middle school math and social studies.
Mrs. Sandusky is a 2003 graduate of Paducah High School and has always been a Dragon at heart. She is joining us from Crowell ISD, and will be teaching English Language Arts in grades 3-5, and 4th grade Social Studies.

Paducah Parents/Athletes, we will be conducting physicals here in Paducah on Tuesday, July 28 at 3:30 PM. This year Physicals are required for all incoming 6th and 7th graders, students new to the district and any student held out due to injury. These physicals will be conducted at the Paducah ISD game gym. Athletes must have the paperwork filled out and signed by a parent prior to arrival. Paperwork is attached to this email and is available at the high school office. All students will be COVID-19 screened and will be required to wear a mask prior to being admitted to the facility. Contact Coach York if you should have questions. All other athletes will need to complete all forms except for the physical portion of the attached UIL forms. The documents are located with the link below. UIL has released information today outlining that school classifications 1A-4A will begin practices on August 3.

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1rhGLXCmxsetmOMBmsj5QxZazAV8m0SwD/view?usp=sharing

Attention:
The Texas Department of Emergency Management (TDEM) is going to perform COVID-19 testing under the white fleet carport at Paducah ISD on Tuesday, July 21st from 10 A.M. until 2 P.M.
There are no pre-requisites and anyone may be tested. You may register on-site. Be able to provide Identification and give name, date of birth, address, phone number, gender, and race per TDEM. The test is the nasal swab with a 2-3 day turnaround. The test is free. We ask that you wear a mask and practice social distancing to keep yourself and others safe.
Thank you!!

Attention:
Next Tuesday, June 30th is the deadline to apply for P-EBT.
P-EBT provides a one-time benefit of up to $285 per eligible child that families can use to purchase food. Eligible families that have children 5-18 years old and received SNAP benefits for March have already received P-EBT benefits. All other eligible families must apply to receive P-EBT benefits.

English link--https://hhs.texas.gov/services/health/coronavirus-covid-19/coronavirus-covid-19-information-texans/pandemic-ebt-p-ebt-due-covid-19

Spanish link--https://hhs.texas.gov/es/servicios/salud/sesion-informativa-de-medicaid-chip-sobre-covid-19/transferencia-electronica-de-beneficios-durante-la-pandemia-p-ebt-por-el-covid-19

Gov. Greg Abbott keeps Texas classrooms closed for remainder of school year

post_text:
Today is Friday, April 17th.

By now all of you are aware that Governor Abbott has extended school closures with distance learning in Texas for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year.

Paducah ISD will continue providing high quality instruction to all of our students through our established distance learning programs.

If you should have any questions about assigned work, all teachers will continue to be available between 8:00 AM and PM 4:00 Monday through Friday. Teachers can be contacted by phone or by sending them an email to their school email address.

We will continue providing meals to those that would like them each Monday morning.

We will be following up with further details and information in the weeks ahead.

It is Great to be a Dragon.

As many of you may have seen or heard, during a press conference held today in Austin, TX, Governor Greg Abbott issued an Executive Order extending social distancing protocols through April 30th and that Texas schools remain closed until May 4th.
Paducah ISD will remain committed to ensuring that your children are given highly qualified instruction via distance learning procedures and meals from our Child Nutrition Department during this difficult time. More information regarding this will be posted here on our facebook page and announced on our school messenger system. We appreciate all that you are doing at home participating in your child's learning process. We are all in this together and will get through it together. Additionally, we appreciate your patience, as this is uncharted waters for all of us as well. Students, we miss you and can't wait until this is over in order to see all of you back in our classrooms and halls again. This Executive Order Supersedes our original school closure announcement and would allow us to begin again with students, on Monday, May 4th.

post_text:
Good Afternoon Dragon Nation,

If you have not responded to the following information, please do.

As we prepare to continue the educational process we need your help. We are developing procedures for delivering your child(s) education through distance learning as well as a means of providing meals for Paducah children ages 0-18. We have a few questions for each of you that will help in this process.

Please respond by sending your answers by email or text to jyork@paducahisd.org

1. What is your name and each of your children and the grade they are currently in at Paducah ISD?

2. Do you and your children have access to the internet?

3. Will you need breakfast/lunches for children ages 0-18?

Thank you for your responses.

We will be sending and posting information about plans for continued education as well as continued cafeteria meal plans Monday, March 23, 2020. This information will be submitted Monday evening through all of our social media outlets. We will be starting our distance learning and meals on Tuesday, March 24, 2020.

March 12 at 4:10 PM ·

The #2020Census is here. 😁 Everyone counts in the census!

Starting today most households across the country will start to receive 2020 Census Invitation Letters that look like this ⬇️ inviting them to go online and complete the 2020 Census!

If you didn’t receive a paper questionnaire, don’t worry. You will get one eventually if you have not responded by April 8.

Don’t forget to count:

✔️ Babies born on or before April 1, 2020, young children, foster or adopted children, grandchildren 👶
✔️ Relatives and non-relatives (your mother-in-law too!) 👵
✔️ Long-term visitors (not abuelita who is visiting for only a couple of days though) 🏠

Questions about the census? Call 📲877-EL-CENSO (352-3676) #HagaseContar

post_text:
Congratulations to Mrs. Michelle Whitaker, who will be retiring at the end of this semester!!!
Paducah ISD wants to publicly thank you for your service and dedication to our students. Mrs. Whitaker began her educational career here at Paducah ISD in 1989. She left for one year in 2010-2011 to be the Director at Dunbar School. She started back at PISD in the Fall of 2011 and has been here ever since. She currently teaches Pre-K, Dyslexia, and is the Head High School and Junior High Cheerleading Sponsor. Many young lives have been molded and shaped by the positive influence of Mrs. Whitaker. She will be greatly missed by her Paducah ISD Family, but we wish her nothing but the best in her retirement!!

Thank You, Mrs. Whitaker,

From Your Paducah ISD Family

post_text: We would like to thank the City of Paducah for allowing the 3rd grade to come and visit City Hall! The 3rd grade class has been discussing the different levels of Government. It was a great opportunity for our kids to meet some of the employees and a representative from the City Council (Richard Gregory). They were able ask questions to tie together what has been discussed in class!

Paducah ISD is offering Senior Citizen athletic event passes for all patrons who are at least 65 years young. You must come to the Superintendent’s office and get your pass from Mrs. Blount during business office hours. The card has a place for an individuals name and will admit that individual to all Paducah ISD Junior High and High School Home Games for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year free of charge. We are only accepting these new cards at the gate.
Thank you and we look forward to seeing you at the next home game!!
